abstract_ssm: Maurice Forge (1902-1990) was a New York bus driver who became an organizer, news editor, and ultimately a vice president of the Transport Workers Union (TWU). In the late 1930s, Forge began organizing the TWU's Airline Transport Division (ATD). A decade later, a union-wide effort to sever TWU ties with the Communist Party resulted in Forge's expulsion from the TWU. The Maurice Forge Papers include materials from Forge's TWU career, including union publicity materials, official correspondence, and transcripts of Forge's TWU hearing and of the government deportation hearing of TWU official John Santo.
